One police officer was injured Monday evening after a fire outbreak at a residential block of Kasarani police station.
 Property worth millions of shillings was destroyed in the fire incident. 
 ALSO READ:

Siwot Secondary School on fire

 Nairobi City County fire brigade and other fire fighters arrived at the scene on time to put off the fire but the upper floor of the building was completely burnt.
 The cause of the fire still unknown but preliminary investigations indicate that it could have been started by a gas explosion in one of the rooms within the building.




